---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="How It Works"
  description="The ShieldEyes architecture: probe, wireless node, gateway, and dashboard — designed for Passive House builders."
>

  {/* Hero */}
  <section class="bg-hero-bg py-24 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-white leading-tight">
        Built for Builders. Designed to Last.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
        ShieldEyes monitors your assembly continuously — from installation day through handoff and beyond.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* Section: The System — 4-step flow */}
  <section class="bg-white py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-text text-center mb-14">The System</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-8">

        <div class="relative flex flex-col">
          <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-green text-white font-bold text-lg flex items-center justify-center">
              1
            </span>
            <div class="flex-1 hidden lg:block h-px bg-gray-200 ml-3"></div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text mb-2">The Probe</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed text-sm">
            A small RH/temperature sensor (SHT40) installed inside the wall assembly at rough framing.
            The probe is positioned in the highest-risk zone — typically between the insulation and sheathing.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="relative flex flex-col">
          <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-green text-white font-bold text-lg flex items-center justify-center">
              2
            </span>
            <div class="flex-1 hidden lg:block h-px bg-gray-200 ml-3"></div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text mb-2">The Wireless Node</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed text-sm">
            The node housing the probe electronics is accessible from inside the building — designed to
            fit through a small penetration in drywall or baseboard, not buried in the wall cavity.
            ~5–6 year battery. Wireless BLE transmission to the gateway.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="relative flex flex-col">
          <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-green text-white font-bold text-lg flex items-center justify-center">
              3
            </span>
            <div class="flex-1 hidden lg:block h-px bg-gray-200 ml-3"></div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text mb-2">The Gateway</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed text-sm">
            A small device (XIAO ESP32-C6) located inside the conditioned space — plugged in, always on.
            Collects data from all nodes in range, adds air quality readings (VOC/PM via SEN54),
            and uploads to the dashboard.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-col">
          <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-green text-white font-bold text-lg flex items-center justify-center">
              4
            </span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text mb-2">The Dashboard</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed text-sm">
            Live and historical graphs of RH, temperature, and dew point for every probe in the
            assembly. Set alert thresholds (e.g. RH &gt; 80% sustained). Accessible from any
            browser at app.shieldeyes.co.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* Section: Key Specs */}
  <section class="bg-section-bg py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-text mb-10">Key Specs</h2>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm overflow-hidden">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <tbody>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-text w-2/5">RH Sensor</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-600">Sensirion SHT40 (&plusmn;1.5% RH, &plusmn;0.2&deg;C)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 bg-gray-50">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-text">Air Quality (Gateway)</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-600">Sensirion SEN54 — PM1/2.5, VOC Index, Temp, Humidity</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-text">Wireless</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-600">BLE (Bluetooth Low Energy)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 bg-gray-50">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-text">Battery Life</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-600">~5–6 years (estimated)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-text">Node Access</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-600">Accessible from conditioned space — never buried</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 bg-gray-50">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-text">Dashboard</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-600">Web-based, browser access, real-time + historical</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-text">Installation</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-600">During rough framing; no rewiring required</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* Section: Designed to Be Serviced */}
  <section class="bg-white py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-text mb-6">
        The unit you won't have to tear open a wall to fix.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed text-lg">
        Every other monitoring solution we evaluated required burying the sensor and accepting that
        it's unserviceable. ShieldEyes is designed from the ground up to be retrieved, inspected,
        and replaced without opening the wall assembly. That's not an afterthought — it's the core
        design constraint.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* CTA */}
  <section class="bg-green py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-10">Ready to protect your builds?</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a
          href="/waitlist"
          class="px-8 py-4 bg-white text-green font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors"
        >
          Join the waitlist
        </a>
        <a
          href="/for-builders"
          class="px-8 py-4 border-2 border-white text-white font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-white hover:text-green transition-colors"
        >
          Read the builder case
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
